datas.name: qualifier
datas.description: The direction of change in the mutant compared to wild type.

datas.name: abnormal
datas.description: The observed phenotype is detectably different from that in the wild type.

datas.name: decreased
datas.description: The observed feature is decreased compared to that in the wild type (slower, weaker, lower, smaller, etc.).

datas.name: absent
datas.description: The observed feature is not detectable in the mutant.

datas.name: increased
datas.description: The observed feature is increased compared to that in the wild type (faster, stronger, higher, larger, etc.).

datas.name: decreased rate
datas.description: Observed feature is decreased with respect to time compared to that in the wild type (slower).

datas.name: increased rate
datas.description: Observed feature is increased with respect to time compared to that in the wild type (faster, accelerated).

datas.name: decreased duration
datas.description: Observed feature occurs over a decreased period of time relative to wild type.

datas.name: increased duration
datas.description: Observed feature occurs over an increased period of time relative to wild type.

datas.name: delayed
datas.description: Observed feature occurs after being postponed for a period of time relative to wild type.

datas.name: arrested
datas.description: Observed feature does not occur in a given time period relative to wild type.

datas.name: premature
datas.description: Observed feature occurs too soon, existing before the proper or usual time compared to wild type.

datas.name: normal
datas.description: The observed phenotype shows no detectable difference between the mutant and the wild type.

datas.name: normal rate
datas.description: Observed feature occurs at the same time relative to wild type.

datas.name: normal duration
datas.description: Observed feature does not change with respect to time compared to that in the wild type.
